        " as an historical fact that a Scotchman involved in the first Jacobite uprising of 1715 was recaptured because, having escaped, he yet lingered near the place of his captivity in the hope of recovering his favorite Titus Livius.      Modern historians have developed their own views of Livy and his place in the ancient world, which were not current in ancient times. For example, one text on Western civilization pronounces: Livy was the prose counterpart of ": null
