        " work consists of two books: the  Chronographia , a summary of history in annalist form, and the Chronikoi Kanones, tables of years and events. St. Jerome translated the tables into Latin as the  Chronicon , probably adding some information of his own from unknown sources. Livys dates appear in Jeromes Chronicon.     The main problem with the information given in the ": null
